        "text": "⇒ [[Graph Theory]] provides a mathematical formalism with which to represent arbitrary relationships among the components of a complex system; as well as a computational aid for discovering latent patterns embedded within those relationships. Social network analysis studies patterns of relationships (such communication, information and resource flow, etc.) among individuals and organizations, and is particularly adept at revealing otherwise “hidden” patterns inside of a network; for example, information-flow bottlenecks and other vulnerabilities of, say, a business organization, that are not obvious from a wire-diagram of its members."
